context: <a1_0><b7_0>Musée Territorial de St.-Barthélemy<b7_0/><a1_0/> is a historical museum known as the "<a0_0>St. Barts Municipal Museum<a0_0/>" also called the "<b5_0><b8_0>Wall House<b8_0/><b5_0/>" (musée – bibliothèque) in <a2_0>Gustavia<a2_0/>, which is located on the far end of La Pointe. The island’s history relating to French, Swedish and <a3_0><b6_0>British<b6_0/><a3_0/> period of occupation is well presented in the museum with photographs, maps and paintings.
